pullRequest.body:
Co-authored-by: Jireh Loreaux <loreaujy@gmail.com>

---
This PR adds various lemmas about the `unitInterval` that might be of interest. 

It would be nice to also have lemmas similar to [Mathlib/Algebra/Order/GroupWithZero/Unbundled](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/GroupWithZero/Unbundled.html), but instantiation `unitInterval` as `PosMulMono` and similar feels weird as unitInterval has no nonnegative values. Maybe there is a clever way to generalize these lemmas? Or we can provide a similar API for `OrderedCommMonoid`? Unfortunately, that would not help with strictness and reflection lemmas. All of these feel not fitting for this PR, however.

This [zulip thread](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/eq.20one.20of.20le.20mul.20in.20the.20unit) is related.

Why are these `sym` rather than `symm`?

```suggestion
theorem le_symm_if_le_symm (i j : I) (h : i â‰¤ Ïƒ j) : j â‰¤ Ïƒ i := by
```
Though it seems like i and j are determined by h, so should be implicit as well

Also below
I think we prefer the `i` to be implicit when the conclusion is an iff
Hmm, there's some `pos_iff_ne_zero` lemmas already; you might match those. Does this need to be simp, though? lt doesn't obviously seem simpler than ne
I think there is argument why lt is more useful, but I won't fight for that. Changed it to `pos_iff_ne_zero` and removed the simp attribute.

Presumably this works
```suggestion
    apply mul_le_mul le_rfl ?_ (nonneg i) (nonneg k)
```
Replace by the output of `simp? [compare, compareOfLessAndEq]` please

```suggestion
@[simp, norm_cast] lemma coe_pos {x : I} : (0 : â„) < x â†” 0 < x := Iff.rfl
@[simp, norm_cast] lemma coe_lt_one {x : I} : (x : â„) < 1 â†” x < 1 := Iff.rfl
```
Same above
If you mean with 'same above' the theorems `coe_ne_zero` and `coe_ne_one` then those are according to the linter not in simp-normal form. Or am I misunderstanding something?
Oh, what are they proved by?

`@unitInterval.coe_ne_zero` simp can prove this: `by simp only [@ne_eq, @Set.Icc.coe_eq_zero]`
`@unitInterval.coe_ne_one` simp can prove this: `by simp only [@ne_eq, @Set.Icc.coe_eq_one]`

```suggestion
lemma symm_eq_one {i : I} : Ïƒ i = 1 â†” i = 0 := by
```
The RHS is implied
I changed it to `symm_eq_one_iff`. Are you fine with that as well?
I would rather remove the `_iff`. It's clearly implied
Alright, I removed it.

```suggestion
  rw [â† symm_zero, symm_bijective.injective.eq_iff]
```
and please make `symm_bijective.injective.eq_iff` a lemma called `symm_inj`

```suggestion
theorem le_symm_comm {i j : I} : i â‰¤ Ïƒ j â†” j â‰¤ Ïƒ i :=
```
Can you first show `Ïƒ j â‰¤ Ïƒ i â†” i â‰¤ j` and `Ïƒ j < Ïƒ i â†” i < j`?

```suggestion
@[norm_cast] theorem coe_ne_zero {x : I} : (x : â„) â‰  0 â†” x â‰  0 := coe_eq_zero.not
@[norm_cast] theorem coe_ne_one {x : I} : (x : â„) â‰  1 â†” x â‰  1 := coe_eq_one.not
```

```suggestion
theorem symm_le_symm {i j : I} : Ïƒ i â‰¤ Ïƒ j â†” j â‰¤ i := by
```

```suggestion
theorem symm_lt_symm {i j : I} : Ïƒ i < Ïƒ j â†” j < i := by
```

```suggestion
lemma lt_one_iff_ne_ {x : I} : x < 1 â†” x â‰  1 := lt_top_iff_ne_top
```
I assume the extra underscore is a typo?
Whoops yes
You should be able to just not specify this

I should, and I assumed this as well.
However, leaving `compare_eq_compareOfLessAndEq` away leaves me with the unsolved case `mk.mk` with goal `compare âŸ¨valâœÂ¹, propertyâœÂ¹âŸ© âŸ¨valâœ, propertyâœâŸ© = compareOfLessAndEq âŸ¨valâœÂ¹, propertyâœÂ¹âŸ© âŸ¨valâœ, propertyâœâŸ©`.

```suggestion
protected lemma pos_iff_ne_zero {x : I} : 0 < x â†” x â‰  0 := bot_lt_iff_ne_bot
```

```suggestion
protected lemma lt_one_iff_ne_one {x : I} : x < 1 â†” x â‰  1 := lt_top_iff_ne_top
```

Please reuse the existing `LinearOrder` instance, and don't override any of its fields. Something like
```
  __ := inferInstanceAs (LinearOrder I)
```
should work. Otherwise we risk introducing two incompatible `LinearOrder I` structures.
Thanks, that worked!
